The paper discusses the development of a multi-agent training framework for interactive learning, which involves communication between agents and humans. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves the development of autonomous agents. The paper also discusses the use of reinforcement learning and imitation learning, which are subfields of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of non-verbal communication and human-computer interaction, which fall under the categories of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper discusses the use of interactive learning for cooperative tasks, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
